These are the minutes for the April 13th, 2011 SPI Board meeting, held
at 20:30 UTC in #spi on irc.spi-inc.org.
[LOG](../../../logs/2011/2011-04-13-log.txt).


## President's Report

Bdale reported that he'd spent some time recently working with a new
representative of the Open64 community, resulting in the resolution
voted on at this meeting.

He was also recently interviewed by the US Department of Justice
anti-trust folks on behalf of Debian. The contents of the interview are
confidential, but he was encouraged by the way they reached out to the
Free Software world for input on a pending matter in this way.


